{"title": "Leakage of sensitive data in JWT", "summary": "  JWTs are not a secure place to store sensitive data. This rule looks for any sensitive data types saved to a JWT. ", "description": "\n\nJWTs are not a secure place to store sensitive data. This rule looks for any sensitive data types saved to a JWT.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid storing sensitive data in JWTs:\n\n```javascript\n  const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');\n  const token = jwt.sign({ user: { email: 'jhon@gmail.com' }});\n```\n\n\u2705 If you need to store user's information, use their unique database identifier instead of personal identifiable information:\n\n```javascript\n  const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');\n  const token = jwt.sign({ user: user.uuid });\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-312"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_lang_jwt", "https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A3_2017-Sensitive_Data_Exposure"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}